   <dlentry class="- topic/dlentry " xtrc="dlentry:7;58:13" xtrf="file:/C:/Git/dita/specification/archSpec/base/basic-concepts.dita">
    <dt class="- topic/dt " xtrc="dt:7;59:9" xtrf="file:/C:/Git/dita/specification/archSpec/base/basic-concepts.dita">Configuration</dt>
    <dd class="- topic/dd " xtrc="dd:7;60:9" xtrf="file:/C:/Git/dita/specification/archSpec/base/basic-concepts.dita"><ph class="- topic/ph " xtrc="ph:12;60:61" xtrf="file:/C:/Git/dita/specification/common/conref-file.dita">A document type shell is an XML grammar
          file that specifies the elements and attributes that are allowed in a DITA document. The
          document type shell integrates structural modules, domain modules, and constraint modules.
          In addition, a document type shell specifies whether and how topics can nest.</ph> See <xref class="- topic/xref " href="configuration.dita" xtrc="xref:7;61:76" xtrf="file:/C:/Git/dita/specification/archSpec/base/basic-concepts.dita" type="concept"><?ditaot gentext?>Configuration<?ditaot genshortdesc?><desc class="- topic/desc ">Configuration enables the definition of DITA document types that include only the   vocabulary modules that are required for a given set of documents. There is no need to modify the   vocabulary modules. Configurations are implemented as document-type shells.</desc></xref> for more
                                        information.</dd>
   </dlentry>
   <dlentry class="- topic/dlentry " xtrc="dlentry:8;64:13" xtrf="file:/C:/Git/dita/specification/archSpec/base/basic-concepts.dita">
